#Text=( ( WSS ) ) What court will it be filed in ?
#Text=Wolfe : It 's going to be filed in Baton Rouge federal court .
#Text=That 's where the jurisdiction is .
#Text=Louisiana Democratic primary by parish .
#Text=President Obama won the parishes in black while Wolfe won the parishes in red .
#Text=Image : William S. Saturn .
#Text=( ( WSS ) )
#Text=If you qualify for delegates in Arkansas and Texas , in light of what happened in Louisiana , what will you do to avoid having those delegates stripped ?
#Text=Wolfe : Well , I do n't think we 'll have the same problems in those states .
#Text=The Louisiana people basically are perpetrating a fraud on the vote .
#Text=The Democratic Party put me up there .
#Text=It was a primary .
#Text=They did n't have to have a primary .
#Text=There was a new law saying the Democratic primary was mandatory .
#Text=It 's a party function .
#Text=They put me on their ballot .
#Text=They accepted my money .

#Text=And then , after that , what they did was have an election , and 17 percent of the people , and this was the Democratic Primary , this was n't an open primary , this was just among registered Democratic voters , and I still got 11 or 12 percent .
#Text=The other guys , there were two other people , together got ten percent : Mr. Ely and Mr. Richardson .

#Text=And then despite all that , despite Obama only taking three quarters , the Democratic Party decided to avert , quite flagrantly , the will of the people and assign all the delegates to Mr. Obama , even though their bylaws , the rules themselves say that the results of the primary are binding .
#Text=Preferential presidential primary results are binding .
#Text=They forsook their own law in order to make it look like there was unanimous support for Obama .
#Text=They want a coronation for him instead of just a nomination .
#Text=They 're treating him again like a king .
#Text=Who does he think he is ? I mean this is ridiculous .
#Text=( ( WSS ) ) You mentioned open primaries , and Texas and Arkansas have open primaries .
#Text=Wolfe : Yeah pretty much open primaries .
#Text=Arkansas definitely and Texas is unless you 're part of the GOP leadership , then you ca n't vote in a Democratic primary .
#Text=But it 's pretty much open and I think that we 'll do fine in both states .
#Text=( ( WSS ) ) So how do you feel about Republican voters that have no interest in their own primary and so vote for you in the Democratic primary to embarrass Obama ?
#Text=Wolfe : Well there 's been no proof yet that that 's happened .
#Text=People say it will happen .
#Text=But I mean , Republicans have their own races .

#Text=And so if they were to vote in the Democratic primary , they would forego the right to vote for local and not only just federal candidates that are Republican , but also local people , because your local primaries in Arkansas are held the same time as the congressional .
#Text=So they would have to basically decide to not vote for anyone they know or like and switch over , just for the purpose of voting against Obama .
#Text=Now whether that 's going to happen or not , I do n't know .
#Text=We can talk about that after the primary to see if it did happen .
